IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SERVING INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES AND INNER-CITY YOUTH
IRS990.MissionDesc: ROCHESTER ROTARY CHARITABLE TRUSTS MAKES A DIFFERENCE IN THE LIVES OF OUR COMMUNITY AND WORLD NEIGHBORS-IN-NEED, WITH SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON CITY YOUTH AND ON INDIVIDUALS OF ALL AGES WITH DISABILITIES.THIS IS DONE THROUGH THE RESOURCES OF OUR SUNSHINE CAMPUS, THE TUESDAY LUNCHEON FORUMS, AND FOCUSED ACTIVITIES COORDINATED THROUGH OUR HEADQUARTERS.ALL ACTIVITIES ARE GUIDED BY THE OBJECTIVES OF ROTARY INTERNATIONAL: FELLOWSHIP, COMMUNITY SERVICE, HIGH ETHICAL STANDARDS, AND INTERNATIONAL UNDERSTANDING AND GOODWILL.
IRS990.Desc: THE ROCHESTER ROTARY SUNSHINE CAMP PROVIDES A CAMPING PROGRAM FOR OVER 2,500 CHILDREN FROM THE GREATER ROCHESTER AND SURROUNDING AREAS AT NO CHARGE TO THE CHILDREN OR THEIR FAMILIES WITHOUT ANY GOVERNMENT FUNDING. ROCHESTER ROTARY HOSTS A TWO WEEK CAMPING PROGRAM FOR CHILDREN WITH SPECIAL NEEDS AGES 7-21 FREE OF CHARGE AND ADDITIONALLY PARTNERS WITH EIGHT AREA AGENCIES TO PROVIDE QUALITY CAMPING PROGRAMS FOR THEIR CAMPERS WITH DISABILITIES. THIS PARTNER USAGE IS SUBSIDIZED BY OUR ORGANIZATION THROUGH GRANTS. THE SUNSHINE CAMP SERVES AS A RESOURCE TO THE ENTIRE COMMUNITY SERVING OVER 5,000 PEOPLE ANNUALLY.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: THE SCHOOL #8 ADOPT-A-SCHOOL PROGRAM PROVIDES ASSISTANCE TO STUDENTS IN THEIR PERSONAL, SOCIAL, AND EDUCATIONAL GROWTH. THE RRCT HAS BEEN COMMITTED TO ROBERTO CLEMENTE SCHOOL IN PARTNERSHIP SINCE 1994.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE PURPOSE OF THE COLLEGE SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR COLLEGE STUDENTS WHO ATTENDED SCHOOL #8. THE STUDENTS ARE MENTORED BY ROTARIANS BEGINNING IN FIFTH GRADE AND CONTINUING THROUGH COLLEGE. THE MENTORS INTRODUCE THE SCHOLARS TO CULTURAL, VOLUNTEER, AND EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES DURING THE MENTOR YEARS.

OtherAssetsOrgGrp.Desc: BENEFICIAL INTEREST IN CHARITABLE REMAINDER TRUST

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CHARITABLE TRUSTS' PERMANENT ENDOWMENT CONSISTS OF THREE FUNDS, ESTABLISHED TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR PRIZES AND AWARDS AT THE SUNSHINE CAMPUS IN MEMORY OF ALDEN I. CLARK, TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR REPAIRS TO THE NATURE TRAIL, AND TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR CAPITAL IMPROVEMENTS TO THE SUNSHINE CAMPUS.

IN ACCORDANCE WITH ASC 740-10-50, ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, THE CHARITABLE TRUSTS RECOGNIZES THE TAX BENEFIT FROM UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY THE TAXING AUTHORITIES. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT THE CHARITABLE TRUSTS IS CURRENTLY OPERATING IN COMPLIANCE WITH THE APPLICABLE REQUIREMENTS OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THEREFORE, NO LIABILITY FOR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS HAS BEEN INCLUDED ON THE CHARITABLE TRUSTS' FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE EXEMPT CHARITABLE TRUSTS' INFORMATIONAL RETURNS ARE SUBJECT TO AUDIT BY VARIOUS TAXING AUTHORITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH YEAR THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS AND SIGNS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A SUBCOMMITTEE MADE UP OF ROCHESTER ROTARY CLUB IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT, CURRENT PRESIDENT, INCOMING PRESIDENT, ROCHESTER ROTARY CHARITABLE TRUSTS PRESIDENT AND ROCHESTER ROTARY CHARITABLE TRUSTS INCOMING PRESIDENT, REVIEWS OTHER EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR COMPENSATION WITHIN ROTARY CLUBS AND OTHER NOT FOR PROFIT ENTITIES. THE COMMITTEE REVIEWS GOALS AND CRITERIA AND COMPLETES A FORMAL EVALUATION FORM. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR ALSO COMPLETES A SELF EVALUATION THAT IS REVIEWED BY THE SUBCOMMITTEE. THE INFORMATION IS THEN SHARED WITH THE ENTIRE JOINT FINANCE COMMITTEE.
